# ----------------------------------------------------------------------
# AzAKSAssessment per-run output (may contain customer-identifying data)
# Layout produced by run.ps1:
#   azaksassessment/reports/<yyyy-MM-dd>_<CustomerName>/
#       <yyyy-MM-dd>_Data/      (collected JSON / CSV — may include
#                                resource IDs, tenant IDs, IPs, names)
#       <yyyy-MM-dd>_Reports/   (HTML reports built from the above)
# Also catches any legacy data/ or reports/ folders if a script is run
# directly without the dated wrapper.
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------
azaksassessment/reports/
azaksassessment/artifacts/[0-9][0-9][0-9][0-9]-[0-9][0-9]-[0-9][0-9]_*/
azaksassessment/artifacts/data/
azaksassessment/artifacts/reports/

# Defensive globs in case the toolchain is copied elsewhere in the repo
**/[0-9][0-9][0-9][0-9]-[0-9][0-9]-[0-9][0-9]_*_Data/
**/[0-9][0-9][0-9][0-9]-[0-9][0-9]-[0-9][0-9]_*_Reports/
**/arg-*.json
**/diagnostic-settings.json
**/diagnostic-errors.json
**/arg-law-resolved.json
**/scope.json
**/scoped-subscriptions.json
**/effective-routes-*.json
**/metrics-*.json
**/kql/
